Distributed System (DS) is one in which

Hardware and software components, located at remote networked computers, coordinate and
communicate their actions only by passing messages. Any distance may separate computers in the
network.

Sharing of resources is the main motivation of distributed systems. Resources may
be managed
by servers and accessed by clients, or they may be encapsulated as objects and accessed by clien
t
objects.
A distributed operating system runs on multiple independent computers, connected through
communication network, but appears to its users as a single virtual machine and runs its own OS
